Date: 0/0/1981
Source: Loughnan Glossary
Author: LOUGHNAN
Vol / Page: 75
Edition:
Quote: solo-man: a solo slaughterman. Before the introduction, in the late 1920s and early 30s, of chain slaughtering, each man did the whole of the killing and dressing. By the 1970s there were very few solo-men still alive.
